  <section>
    <h2>Basic Usage</h2>
    <p>Wrap any HTML table with <code>&lt;table-wc&gt;</code> and add data attributes to enable features. The table structure remains semantic and accessible.</p>

    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Sortable columns example">{{ sortableColumnsCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Sorting</h2>
    <p>Add <code>data-sort</code> to any <code>&lt;th&gt;</code> element to make that column sortable. Click the column header to cycle through ascending, descending, and unsorted states.</p>

    <h3>Sort Types</h3>
    <table class="props-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Value</th>
          <th>Description</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><code>string</code></td>
          <td>Alphabetical sorting (case-insensitive)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>number</code></td>
          <td>Numeric sorting (handles decimals and negatives)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>date</code></td>
          <td>Date sorting (parses common date formats)</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h3>Custom Sort Values</h3>
    <p>Use <code>data-sort-value</code> on cells when the display value differs from the sort value (e.g., formatted currency or dates).</p>

    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Custom sort values">{{ customSortValuesCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Filtering</h2>
    <p>Add <code>data-filterable</code> to the table to enable text filtering. A search input is automatically generated above the table. Rows that don't match the filter text are hidden.</p>

    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Filterable table">{{ filterableCode | escape }}</code-block>

    <aside class="note">
      <strong>Tip:</strong> Try typing "engineering" or "new york" in the filter to see matching rows.
    </aside>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Pagination</h2>
    <p>Add <code>data-paginate="n"</code> to the table to show only <code>n</code> rows per page. Pagination controls are automatically generated below the table.</p>

    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Paginated table">{{ paginatedCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Row Expansion</h2>
    <p>Create expandable rows by adding <code>data-expandable</code> to a row and following it with a <code>data-expand-content</code> row. A toggle button is automatically added to control the expansion.</p>

    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Expandable rows">{{ expandableRowsCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Row Selection</h2>
    <p>Add checkboxes to rows for selection, with a "select all" checkbox in the header and a bulk actions bar that appears when rows are selected.</p>

    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Row selection with bulk actions">{{ rowSelectionCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Responsive Card Mode</h2>
    <p>Add <code>data-responsive="card"</code> to transform the table into a card layout on narrow screens. Use <code>data-label</code> on cells to show column headers in card mode.</p>

    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Responsive card layout">{{ responsiveCardCode | escape }}</code-block>

    <aside class="note">
      <strong>Note:</strong> The layout switches based on viewport width. In production, it adapts automatically.
    </aside>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Sticky Headers and Columns</h2>
    <p>Use <code>data-layout-sticky</code> to keep headers or columns visible while scrolling.</p>

